FAQs about hotels in Orlando

On average, 3-star hotels in Orlando cost $123 per night, and 4-star hotels in Orlando are $207 per night. If you're looking for something really special, a 5-star hotel in Orlando can be found for $459 per night, on average (based on Booking.com prices).
The average price per night for a 3-star hotel in Orlando this weekend is $164 or, for a 4-star hotel, $280. Looking for something even fancier? 5-star hotels in Orlando for this weekend cost around $605 per night, on average (based on Booking.com prices).
On average, it costs $132 per night to book a 3-star hotel in Orlando for tonight. You'll pay around $241 if you choose to stay in a 4-star hotel tonight, while a 5-star hotel in Orlando will cost around $1,053, on average (based on Booking.com prices).
Many families visiting Orlando loved staying at Hampton Inn By Hilton Ocoee Orlando, Residence Inn by Marriott Orlando East/UCF Area, and Marriott's Royal Palms.
Some of the best hotels in Orlando near Downtown Disney include Drury Plaza Hotel Orlando - Disney Springs Area, Marriott's Sabal Palms and Sheraton Vistana Resort Villas, Lake Buena Vista Orlando.
Travelers who stayed in Orlando near Orlando International Airport (MCO) have said good things about Hyatt Regency Orlando International Airport Hotel, Hyatt House Orlando Airport, and Marriott Orlando Airport Lakeside.
Hyatt House Orlando Airport, Drury Plaza Hotel Orlando - Disney Springs Area, and Residence Inn by Marriott Orlando at FLAMINGO CROSSINGS Town Center are some of the popular hotels in Orlando.
For hotels in Orlando that serve highly-rated breakfasts, try Hampton Inn Orlando Southeast Nona, Marriott's Harbour Lake, and Marriott's Royal Palms.
